eu.toolchain.concurrent

Class CoreAsync

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.toolchain.concurrent.CoreAsync
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Async

    public class CoreAsync
extends Object
implements Async
    Entry point to the tiny async framework.

    Example usage: 

    
   final Async async = CoreAsync.builder().build();

      • completable

        public <T> Completable<T> completable()
        Description copied from interface: Async
        Build a new resolvable completable.

        The completable is returned in a running state, and can be completed, failed, or cancelled. See documentation for Stage for details on the various states.

        These futures are guaranteed to be thread-safe, all of their methods can be called from any thread, at any time.

        Specified by:
        completable in interface Async
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the completable.
        Returns:
        A new resolvable completable.

      • streamCollect

        public <T,U> Stage<U> streamCollect(Collection<? extends Stage<? extends T>> futures,
                                    StreamCollector<? super T,? extends U> collector)
        Description copied from interface: Async
        Build a new stage that is the result of applying a computation on a collection of futures.

        This is similar to Async.collect(Collection, Function), but uses StreamCollector which operates on the stream of results as they arrive.

        This allows the implementor to reduce memory usage for certain operations since all results does not have to be collected.

        If the returned stage ends up in a non-completed state, this will be forwarded to the given list of futures as well.

        Specified by:
        streamCollect in interface Async
        Type Parameters:
        T - source type of the collected futures.
        U - target type of the collector
        Parameters:
        futures - the collection of futures
        collector - the collector
        Returns:
        a stage bound to the collected value of the collector

      • eventuallyCollect

        public <C,T> Stage<T> eventuallyCollect(Collection<? extends Callable<? extends Stage<? extends C>>> callables,
                                        StreamCollector<? super C,? extends T> collector,
                                        int parallelism)
        Description copied from interface: Async
        Collect the result from a collection of operations that are lazily created.

        Async will be created using the given callables, but will only create as many pending futures to be less than or equal to the given parallelism setting.

        If a single completable is cancelled, or failed, all the other will be as well.

        This method is intended to be used for rate-limiting requests that could potentially be difficult to stop cleanly.

        Specified by:
        eventuallyCollect in interface Async
        Type Parameters:
        C - source type of the collected futures
        T - target type the collected futures are being transformed into
        Parameters:
        callables - the collection of operations
        collector - the collector
        parallelism - number of futures that are allowed to be pending at the same time
        Returns:
        a new completable that is completed when all operations are completed
